{
  "stem": "24106.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But when we got up, the children to go to school, the latkes were already on the table.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We did tea.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's what my mother was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Could you describe Purim?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Purim?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, Purim.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Purim.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had a yeshiva by us, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The yeshiva boys used to come.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They used to make like they go to the houses and they make a play.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[SPEAKING YIDDISH] They come to the house, and they had a little corner, and they-- they'd perform.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They perform for us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's-- that's Purim for us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then, you know, we had a Purim seudat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My mother used to bake a challah, a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was like a half a table.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then she makes, you know, like-- either she makes a goose probably for the seudat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And everybody come to the Purim seudat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "All the family-- especially my mother's brothers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They used to come to us with the family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Purim was-- And then as I grow older, they used to make a Purim ball from the Zionist organizations.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And used to dress up in different kind of costumes, and we went out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was-- it was something looking forward.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think it once we had like in-- from-- from the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had like a play.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] is like-- is a lover.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like a lover.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] means love.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So afterwards, dressed up with, you know, pants and with a lot of sequins, and with crowns on the head.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Different kind of-- you know, the children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, it was really-- you have to make it your own.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I didn't know what my other friend was going to wear, so I have to be very careful.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pesach.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Pesach.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
